Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Mix cream cheese spread and 1 cup of the shredded cheese. Spread onto bottom of 9-inch pie plate; top with salsa and remaining 1/2 cup shredded cheese. Bake 25 minutes or until dip is heated through and cheese is melted. Top with olives, peppers and sour cream. Serve as a hot dip with crackers.